import React, { useState } from "react";

function Counter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  function handleIncrement() {
    setCount(count + 1);
  }

  function handleDecrement() {
    setCount(count - 1);
  }

  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{count}</h1>
      <button onClick={handleIncrement}>+</button>
      <button onClick={handleDecrement}>-</button>
    </div>
  );
}

export default Counter;
```

This component displays a counter with two buttons that allow the user to increment or decrement the counter. It uses the `useState` hook to manage the state of the counter, and two event handler functions to update the state when the buttons are clicked. 

To use this component, you would typically import it in another file and include it in your app's component tree. When the user clicks the buttons, the state of the counter will be updated and the component will re-render with the new count value.

